author: philip
msg: Fix a path canonicalization bug, and a knock-on feedback bug.  The WC locking
code now assumes paths are canonical.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/path.c
(svn_path_get_longest_ancestor): Canonicalize output.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/lock.c
(adm_access_alloc): Duplicate the path.
(svn_wc_adm_open, svn_wc_adm_retrieve): Don't canonicalize the path.
* subversion/libsvn_client/commit.c
(svn_client_commit): Pass common ancestor not a length (so no longer
need a +1 to represent a separator).
* subversion/libsvn_client/commit_util.c
(do_item_commit): Use common ancestor to get relative feedback path.
(svn_client__do_commit): Change parameter from offset to path.
* subversion/libsvn_client/client.h
(svn_client__do_commit): Change parameter from offset to path.
